parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause the vehicle to shake violently, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or wobbles violently when hitting a bump or pothole
especially at high speeds; the steering wheel becomes loose or difficult to control; the vehicle may pull to one side or vibrate excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of steering components can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes loose or difficult to control; the vehicle pulls to one side or vibrates excessively; the steering system makes a loud noise or feels rough.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn or feels heavy; the power steering system makes a loud noise or feels rough; the vehicle loses power steering assist.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TIPM can cause a range of electrical issues, including malfunctioning headlights, turn signals, brake lights, and interior lights, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Malfunctioning headlights
turn signals
brake lights
and interior lights
intermittent wiper function
stuck or malfunctioning gauges
and engine stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the computer-controlled vehicle charging system can cause the passenger-side battery to overcharge, leading to swelling and potentially an engine fire.
symptoms: The dash gauge indicates overcharging
the battery swells
and the vehicle is unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbag did not deploy in an accident
airbag light is on
horn and cruise control do not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata airbag recall can lead to a higher risk of accidents and injuries due to the faulty airbag inflators.
symptoms: Received recall notice
but parts are not available
dealer unable to repair
multiple attempts to schedule repair
lack of communication from manufacturer and dealer.
